  "text": "The hydrophobic membrane is suitable for the TOEC process. Thus, the surface hydrophobicity of the membrane was evaluated by the water contact angle measurement. These results are shown in Figure 3 . It was clearly found that the contact angle increased with the addition of the graphene. This should be due to the significant hydrophobicity of the graphene. Introducing the graphene in the PVDF endows a more hydrophobic surface than the pure PVDF membrane. The similar results have been observed in polymer/graphene composites [CITATION_1] . Therefore, the incorporation of graphene in PVDF can improve the surface hydrophobicity, which is helpful for the TOEC process. ",
